  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Site Safety Supervisor with Earthwork related Experiences",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Roles &amp; Responsibilities</strong></u></p>\n<p>● Monitor and inspect work sites to ensure that safe work practices are carried out in all work operations and compliant with the OSHA, ISO &amp; WSH Act requirements.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>● Report instances of WSH non-compliance, unsafe work conditions and practices to team members.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>● Ensures safety documents in order to Main contractors in collaboration with Safety Officer on site</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>● Ensures that site works have proper safety documents and follow correct safety procedures, conduct toolbox meetings and ensure site safety procedures are followed.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>● Maintains site safe and clean working environment by enforcing internal procedures, rules, and regulations.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>● Contributes to project team effort by accomplishing related results as needed</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>● Proficient in Risk assessment (RA) and Method of Statement (MOM) methodology.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>● Proficient on Earthwork excavation and disposal</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Requirements</strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Advance Certificate in Workplace Safety and Health</li>\n  <li>Familiar with the statutory requirements related to WSH Act and other aspect of safety</li>\n  <li>At least 3 years of safety and work experiences in Earthwork field</li>\n  <li>A team player and ability to work independently and influence others</li>\n  <li>Work Permit preferred</li>\n  <li>Salary commensurate with experience</li>\n</ul>",
